Package dubstep.solution.plan

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Aggregate
    A concrete implementation of a relational plan operator representing a aggregate operator.
    Aggregate.AggColumn
    A utility structure for storing aggregate function details Specifically, stores the - Name of the aggregate (e.g., "C" for the expression "SELECT COUNT(*) AS C FROM ...") - Expression arguments of the aggregate (["A"] in "SELECT SUM("A") AS TOT FROM ..."") - Type of the aggregate (e.g., SUM, COUNT, etc...)
    CrossProduct
    A concrete implementation of a relational plan operator representing a cross product
    FileScan
    A concrete implementation of a relational plan operator representing a file scan operator.
    Limit
    A concrete implementation of a relational plan operator representing a limit operator.
    NullSource
    A concrete implementation of a relational operator corresponding to a virtual 'null' relation.
    Operator
    An abstract implementation of functionality common to all nodes in a relational query plan.
    Operator.Binary
    An abstract implementation of a Operator that reads from two input relations Only operator-specific methods should need to be implemented in subclasses.
    Operator.Leaf
    An abstract implementation of a Operator that reads from no input relations Only operator-specific methods should need to be implemented in subclasses.
    Operator.Unary
    An abstract implementation of a Operator that reads from one input relation Only operator-specific methods should need to be implemented in subclasses.
    Projection
    A concrete implementation of a relational plan operator representing a projection operator (technically projection and renaming operators rolled into one).
    Projection.Target  
    Selection
    A concrete implementation of a relational plan operator representing a selection operator.
    Sort
    A concrete implementation of a relational plan operator representing an ORDER BY clause.
    Sort.Ordering
    A sort order consisting of an expression to compute the value of interest (e.g., a column) and a marker of whether the column should be sorted in ascending or descending order.
    Union
    A concrete implementation of a relational plan operator representing a union operator.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Aggregate.AType  
    Operator.Structure
    An enumerator for classifying the structural type of a plan node - Leaf nodes read from no relations and should be subclasses of Leaf.
    Operator.Type
    The explicit type of a plan node.
